Cell annotation

2023-04-22

The next stage after pre-processing is to cluster the data and then use marker genes to annotate the clusters.

Data availability: Publicly available data used in this document can be accessed at http://neuroblastomacellatlas.org.

The above data was originally used in the following publication:
Tumor to normal single-cell mRNA comparisons reveal a pan-neuroblastoma cancer cell - Kildisuite et al.2021

Import marker genes and files

Read in the Excel files using the readxl package: Convert from Seurat object to SingleCellExperiment object using Seurat object

celltype_markers <- read_excel('./markers/cell_markers.xlsx',col_names = TRUE)
mes_adr_markers <- read_excel('./markers/mes_adr.xlsx',col_names = TRUE)

seurat <- readRDS(file = 'Datasets/Kildisuite/kildisuite_annotated_seurat')
sce <- as.SingleCellExperiment(seurat)

Add clinical data into the dataset

Clinical data is included as a separate file, although its possible to integrate extra information into the SingleCellExperiment metadata. I re-formatted the clinical data prior to integration:

patientdata <- read_excel('datasets/Kildisuite/kildisuite_patientdata.xlsx',col_names = TRUE)

sce$treatment <- sce$SampleName
sce$risk <- sce$SampleName
sce$INSS <- sce$SampleName
sce$MYCN_status <- sce$SampleName

for(i in 1:28 ){
  sce$treatment[sce$treatment == patientdata[[i,1]]] <- patientdata[[i,2]]
  sce$risk[sce$risk == patientdata[[i,1]]] <- patientdata[[i,3]]
  sce$INSS[sce$INSS == patientdata[[i,1]]] <- patientdata[[i,4]]
  sce$MYCN_status[sce$MYCN_status == patientdata[[i,1]]] <- patientdata[[i,5]]
}  

#To view the last line of the metadata:
tail(as.data.frame(colData(sce)),1)

Clustering

Perform clustering using the scran and bluster package:

#Cluster with leiden method 
#We set a seed since leiden clustering is stochastic
set.seed(100)
#The value of k=60 was chosen arbitrarily, to yield a reasonable number of clusters for manual annotating
sce$leiden <- clusterCells(sce, 
                           use.dimred = "PCA", 
                           BLUSPARAM = SNNGraphParam(k = 60, 
                                                     cluster.fun = "leiden"))

table(sce$leiden)

Dimensionality reduction

#Plot TSNE (stochastic)
#Set seed for reproducible analyses 
set.seed(100)
sce <- runTSNE(sce, 
               perplexity = 50, 
               dimred = "PCA",
               n_dimred = 10)


#Plot UMAP (stochastic)
#Set seed for reproducible analyses
set.seed(100)
sce <- runUMAP(sce, 
               dimred = "PCA",
               n_neighbors = 50,
               n_dimred = 10)

Conversion to Seurat object

sce.seurat <- as.Seurat(sce, counts = "counts", data = "logcounts")

#Set main Seurat label to the cluster numbers
sce.seurat <- SetIdent(sce.seurat, value = "leiden")

Dimensionality reduction plots

PCA

#PCA plot coloured by batch
png("plots/PCA_batch.png",width = 230, height = 180, units='mm', res = 600)
DimPlot(sce.seurat, reduction = "PCA", group.by = "SampleName") + 
  ggtitle("PCA by batch") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size=22,hjust = 0.5)) +
  xlab("PC1") + ylab("PC2") +
  labs(color = "Sample Name") 
dev.off()

#PCA plot coloured by cluster, not yet annotated
png("plots/PCA_cluster.png",width = 230, height = 180, units='mm', res = 600)
DimPlot(sce.seurat, reduction = "PCA", label = TRUE, repel = TRUE) +
  ggtitle("PCA by cluster") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size=22,hjust = 0.5)) +
  xlab("PC1") + ylab("PC2") +
  labs(color = "Cluster Number") 
dev.off()

Note: If batch correction is performed, the batch-corrected co-ordinates are used ONLY for visualisation purposes, not for downstream quantitative analyses.
